  <rte>
    <name>Beacon Fell and Beacon Tarn circular</name>
	<desc>This outlying Wainwright has an attractive tarn, Beacon Tarn, at its foot, the relative shallowness of which (maximum depth 26 feet) has earned it a bit of a reputation for wild swimming in summer.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1058-description</url>
